&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; angaza_users &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;AS&lt;/span&gt; angaza
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;RIGHT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;JOIN&lt;/span&gt; accounts &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;AS&lt;/span&gt; acc
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;ON&lt;/span&gt; acc.responsible_user_angaza_id &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; angaza.user_angaza_id;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;union-and-full-join&#34;&gt;UNION and Full Join:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A union combines the rows of two similar queries into a single result with no duplicates. The keyword UNION is placed between the queries. The ORDER BY clause, if used, must specify column positions and appear in the final query only.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
